about the current Russo-Japanese relations.

133
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,020
Really?

134
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,310
If they wanted to arrest me,

135
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,410
they should've done it yesterday.

136
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:26,480
But the thing is,

137
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:29,720
what's the use of arresting me?

138
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,480
When Sun Wen was arrested in London,

139
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,159
it shook the world.

140
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:35,830
But before that,

141
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,360
who outside China

142
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,270
had even heard of a Chinese man named Sun Wen?

143
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:40,330
If that's the case,

144
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,360
Hanhua,

145
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:42,630
maybe...

146
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,930
tomorrow you'll be the next Sun Wen.

147
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:50,870
I've heard Japanese generals

148
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:51,870
aren't very tall.

149
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:53,070
Is that true?

150
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:57,360
He's short and plain-looking.

151
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:59,040
His skin is tanned.

152
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,420
When he thinks,

153
00:08:00,490 --> 00:08:02,370
he looks no different from a farmer.

154
00:08:02,370 --> 00:08:03,890
But when he looks at you,

155
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,720
when he listens to you,

156
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,380
his eyes are like a hawk's.

157
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:10,780
He carefully listens to every word you say,

158
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:12,480
and you can feel

159
00:08:12,630 --> 00:08:14,360
his burning ambition.

160
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:16,760
You're very perceptive, Mr. Yang.

161
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,390
I've been in Japan for years,

162
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:19,160
and that is something

163
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,390
I know well too.

164
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,690
That's exactly why things need to change.

165
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,600
Liang Xiang,

166
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:27,120
with your status,

167
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,380
it's quite impressive

168
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,180
that you can realize this.

169
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,730
The key is how to change things?

170
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:36,840
Change from following heaven's will
to following the people's will.

171
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,870
Change is a must.

172
00:08:37,890 --> 00:08:39,440
Of course, it has to be for the Emperor.

173
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:42,030
Right now, there's change in politics
and in the military.

174
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,289
Political change means reform,

175
00:08:43,289 --> 00:08:45,490
and military change means revolution.

176
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:48,450
So, Mr. Yang, do you advocate for reform

177
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,960
or revolution?

178
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,630
What do you think?

179
00:08:54,160 --> 00:08:56,240
China needs gradual reform.

180
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,770
A revolution will just throw China

181
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,960
from the frying pan into the fire.

182
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:05,080
It seems that your military school

183
00:09:05,630 --> 00:09:07,960
teaches more than just military affairs.

184
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,840
In Tokyo alone,

185
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,840
there are nearly 10,000

186
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,100
Chinese students now.

187
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,480
You can meet Chinese students everywhere.

188
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:18,210
Once you meet them,
you can't avoid these topics.

189
00:09:18,270 --> 00:09:19,600
Now, Chinese politics

190
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,720
is something everyone wants to participate in.

191
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:22,480
Everyone

192
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:24,150
thinks they have a say in it.

193
00:09:32,670 --> 00:09:33,800
Where is this place?

194
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,280
How did we end up here?

195
00:09:35,730 --> 00:09:37,150
Are you asking us?

196
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,680
I was going to ask you.

197
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,480
Did you

198
00:09:40,510 --> 00:09:41,770
do something illegal?

199
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:48,740
Are we at the police department?

200
00:09:48,910 --> 00:09:50,240
What happened exactly?

201
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,870
I... I need to take a leak.

202
00:10:01,490 --> 00:10:02,450
Listen up!

203
00:10:02,770 --> 00:10:05,050
Each of you needs to register here.

204
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:06,320
After that,

205
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,320
you'll need someone to bail you out.

206
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,060
Excuse me.

207
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,550
Why exactly

208
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:14,120
are you detaining us?

209
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,390
You didn't even interrogate us,

210
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,670
yet you want us to call someone to bail us out?

211
00:10:16,670 --> 00:10:17,480
Cut the crap!

212
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,090
If I tell you to register, then register.

213
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:20,900
If I tell you to find someone, then find someone!

214
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,420
You know what this is about.

215
00:10:26,790 --> 00:10:28,360
That's enough for today.

216
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,010
Let me help you.

217
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:42,220
Thank you.

218
00:11:00,690 --> 00:11:01,600
Miss Shuhong.

219
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,440
Yes?

220
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:07,960
Are you married?

221
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:11,720
No.

222
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:15,870
Have you ever...

223
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,910
been with someone?

224
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:27,390
I don't mean anything else by it.

225
00:11:27,990 --> 00:11:28,800
It's just that...

226
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:31,990
I see a kind of maternal instinct in you,

227
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,720
which is rare to see in someone your age.

228
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:41,270
Is that good or bad?

229
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:46,080
I'm not trying to interfere with your life.

230
00:11:46,450 --> 00:11:48,450
Even if you wanted to, it's too late.

231
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,510
Give me your hand.

232
00:11:53,270 --> 00:11:54,200
Let me see.

233
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:01,600
What a beautiful hand.

234
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:08,110
It shows that your figure is elegant.

235
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:12,670
They say your hands match your figure.

236
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,600
Really?

237
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:20,360
We should have a proper chat sometime.

238
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:23,910
I have a good impression of you.

239
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:26,920
