408
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:47,310
What do you take this place for?

409
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:51,000
Your private club?

410
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:54,640
No, it's a misunderstanding.

411
00:24:55,310 --> 00:24:57,400
Let me explain.

412
00:24:58,220 --> 00:24:59,650
Explain what?

413
00:25:01,070 --> 00:25:02,200
You're an educated person,

414
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,440
how could you do something like this?

415
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:08,480
The check you pawned at my Yokohama Specie Bank

416
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,680
was actually forged.

417
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:12,590
Do you think I'm an idiot?

418
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,830
No.

419
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:20,490
That's right!

420
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:24,050
It's forged, totally forged!

421
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:30,160
You're pretty tough, huh?

422
00:25:30,580 --> 00:25:32,210
Let's see

423
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:35,480
if your neck's tougher than my knife.

424
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:47,200
Bastard!

425
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,960
It wasn't me!

426
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:52,270
It's Mr. Kanyama.

427
00:25:54,310 --> 00:25:56,760
It's Mr. Kanyama of the Black Tiger.

428
00:25:56,790 --> 00:25:57,590
Wait.

429
00:25:59,310 --> 00:26:00,550
Mr. Kanyama?

430
00:26:01,030 --> 00:26:01,790
Yes.

431
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:05,070
The one who runs a stationery store?

432
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,270
Yes.

433
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:12,530
The one who sells paintings, counterfeit money,

434
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:17,560
and also four treasures of the study.

435
00:26:31,610 --> 00:26:34,610
Why are we in such a place?

436
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:38,410
